	//--></script><noscript><img alt="image" src="/images/location.jpg"></noscript></div><div class="lefthandnav"><ul id="mainlinks"><div class="currentpage">Hotel Home Page</div><div><a href="/weblet/relocate?FromURL=reslink&#38;ToURL=https%3A%2F%2Fwarwickhotels.ibe.netbooker.com%2Fweb%2FFrontController.nb4%3Fmodule%3DPropertySearch%26operation%3DSinglePropertySearch%26execute%3Dyes%26propertyCodeType%3DRV%26chainCode%3DWK%26instanceId%3D61%26propertyCode%3D061265%26lookAndFeelId%3D599" target="Reservations">Reservations</a></div><div><a href="/s17145/location.html" target="_top">New York Information &amp; Map</a></div><div><a href="/s17145/accommodation.html" target="_top">Rooms &amp; Suites</a></div><div><a href="/s17145/offers.html" target="_top">Special Offers &amp; Packages</a></div><div><a href="/s17145/restaurants_bars.html" target="_top">Restaurants &amp; Bars</a></div><div><a href="/s17145/meetings.html" target="_top">Meetings &amp; Conferences</a></div><div><a href="/s17145/facilities.html" target="_top">Hotel Facilities &amp; Services</a></div><div><a href="/s17145/photo.html" target="_top">Hotel Photo Tour</a></div><div><a href="/s17145/brochure.html" target="_top">Hotel Brochure</a></div><div><a href="javascript:void(window.open('http://www.warwickhotels.com/contact_us.html','email','height=500,width=770,resizable,scrollbars'));" target="_self">More Information</a></div></ul><tr><td align="left" colspan="2" height="12" valign="bottom"></td></tr><a href="http://www.warwickhotels.com/" target="_blank"><img alt="Warwick International Hotels" class="warwicklogo" src="/images/warwicklogo.gif"></a><br><img alt="alternative logo" class="logo2" src="/images/logo2.gif"></div><img alt="hotel tagline" class="tagline" src="/images/tagline.gif"><h2>The Warwick New York Hotel</h2><div class="content"><P>Welcome to The Warwick New York Hotel, a palatial midtown Manhattan hotel, perfectly located close to Broadway and numerous New York City landmarks. Commissioned by William Randolph Hearst in 1926 for his paramour, Marion Davies, to host their many Hollywood and theatrical friends, The Warwick New York Hotel was originally built opposite the Ziegfeld Theater for this very reason.</P>
<P>The Warwick New York Hotel epitomises European-style elegance and is convenient for both business and vacation travellers to see New York City at its greatest. The hotel stands across the street from New York's newly revitalised Museum of Modern Art (MoMA) and is within four blocks of New York City's Broadway, Central Park, Carnegie Hall, Fifth Avenue and the Rockefeller Center. Easily accessible from New York's airports, the hotel offers an intimate atmosphere and personalised service for today's traveller.</P>
<P>The Warwick New York Hotel offers 359 oversized hotel guest <A href="http://warwickhotelny.com/s17145/rooms.html">rooms</A>, 67 handsomely appointed <A href="http://warwickhotelny.com/s17145/suites.html">suites</A> (several with terraces), non-smoking rooms, marble bathrooms, special amenities, high-speed wireless Internet, dual-line telephones, minibar, in-room safes, Business Centre, Fitness Centre, valet service, 24-hour Room Service and full-sized meeting and banquet facilities.</P>
<P>For dining and enjoyment, The Warwick New York Hotel has recently opened its restaurant, <A href="http://www.murals54.com/">Murals on 54</A>, featuring innovative continental cuisine with international influences. <A href="http://warwickhotelny.com/s17145/randolphs_bar.html">Randolph's Bar</A>, designed to closely resemble a living room rather than a hotel bar, with inviting sofas and armchairs, is an excellent venue to see and be seen in Manhattan.</P>
<P>Throughout the years, The Warwick New York has retained its revered name as one of the best New York City hotels and has always appealed to celebrities. The New York City choice of hotel for The Beatles, Cary Grant's Manhattan home for 12 years and even 'The King', Elvis Presley, made The Warwick New York his home when he visited New York. For a more detailed account of The Warwick's location and unique history, please click <A href="http://warwickhotelny.com/s17145/location_history.html">here</A>.</P>
<P>The Warwick New York Hotel is proud to be affiliated with the National Trust for Historic Preservation's <A href="http://www.historichotels.org/" target=_blank>Historic Hotels of America</A>. </P><div class="contentfooter"></div></div>
